According to the ''{{ill|Sendai Kuji Hongi|ja|先代旧事本紀|12=draft}}'' ("Records of Ancient Matters"), the office of Ukita no Kuni no Miyatsuko was established during the reign of {{ill|Emperor Seimu|ja|成務天皇|12=draft}}, appointing '''{{ill|Kagawaki|ja|賀我別王|12=draft}}''', a fifth-generation descendant of {{ill|Emperor Sujin|ja|崇神天皇|12=draft}}, as the first ruler of the region.

=== Clan ===
The clan name was '''{{ill|Kimikobe clan|ja|吉弥侯部|12=draft}}''' (read "Kimikobe Uji"). They were kin to the {{ill|Kamitsukeno clan|ja|上毛野氏|1=Kamitsukeno clan|12=draft}}, {{ill|Shimotsukeno clan|ja|下毛野氏|1=Shimotsukeno clan|lt=Shimotsukeno clan|12=draft}}, and other related clans such as the {{ill|Harima Kamo clan|ja|針間鴨国造|12=draft}}. In the first year of {{ill|Jingō-keiun|ja|神護景雲|12=draft}} (767 CE), on {{nihongo|July 19|7月19日}}, Kimikobe Ishimaro (吉弥侯部石麻呂), a resident of {{ill|Uda District|ja|宇多郡|12=draft}}, was granted the surname of "Kamitsukeno Mutsu no Kimi" (上毛野陸奥公).

== Territory ==

=== Domain ===
The Ukita no Kuni no Miyatsuko governed the region known as "Ukita Province," which later became part of {{ill|Mutsu Province|ja|Mutsu Province|12=draft}}. The domain encompassed areas in {{ill|Uda District|ja|宇多郡|12=draft}} and {{ill|Nakama District, Fukushima|ja|行方郡|12=draft}}, corresponding to modern {{ill|Sōma, Fukushima|ja|相馬市|12=draft}}, {{ill|Minamisōma|ja|南相馬市|12=draft}}, and parts of {{ill|Shinchi, Fukushima|ja|新地町|12=draft}} and {{ill|Iitate, Fukushima|ja|飯舘村|12=draft}} in Fukushima Prefecture. Neighboring domains at the time included the {{ill|Iku no Kuni no Miyatsuko|ja|伊久国造|12=draft}} to the northwest and the {{ill|Someha no Kuni no Miyatsuko|ja|染羽国造|12=draft}} to the south.

During the reforms following the {{ill|Taika Reforms|ja|大化の改新|12=draft}}, the regions were restructured, with the Uda River valley forming Uda District and the Nitta River valley forming Nakama District.<ref>Hirakawa Minami, ''Ancient History of the Tōhoku "Kaido,"'' Iwanami Shoten, 2012, p. 122.</ref>

== Religious Significance ==

=== Clan Shrine ===
The sole {{ill|Shikinaisha|ja|式内社|1=Shikinaisha|12=draft}} and {{ill|Myōjin-taisha|ja|名神大社|fr|Myōjin Taisha|zh|名神大社|12=draft}} in {{ill|Uda District|ja|宇多郡|12=draft}} is the '''{{ill|Komidake Shrine|ja|子眉嶺神社|12=draft}}''', believed to be associated with the Ukita no Kuni no Miyatsuko.

=== Kofuns ===

* '''{{ill|Sakurai Kofun|ja|桜井古墳|12=draft}}'''
: Located in {{ill|Minamisōma|ja|南相馬市|12=draft}}, Fukushima Prefecture, this keyhole-shaped tumulus (全長74メートル) dates to the late 4th or early 5th century. It is considered the possible burial site of {{ill|Kagawaki|ja|鹿我別命|12=draft}}, the clan's progenitor.<ref>Hōga Toshio, "[http://wwr2.ucom.ne.jp/hetoyc15/hitori/kimikobe1.htm Genealogy of the Kimikobe-surnamed Madara Clan]," 2016.</ref>

* '''{{ill|Mano Kofungun|ja|真野古墳群|12=draft}}'''
: Also located in Minamisōma, this large cluster of Kofuns from the late Kofun period includes two keyhole-shaped tumuli and numerous circular mounds.

